<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7330&amp;p=72060#p72060</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7330&amp;p=72060#p72060"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[What's the deal with the APU's 89490 divider?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7330&amp;p=72060#p72060"><![CDATA[
On the Wiki and in Blargg's apu_ref.txt block we get a statement like this:<br /><br />"The version of the CPU in NTSC and RGB systems divides the 21.47727 MHz system clock by 89490."<br /><br />Why 89490?<br /><br />21.47727M / 89490 = 239.9963Hz<br /><br />But with <strong>89489</strong> we get...<br /><br />21.47727M / 89489 = 239.9989Hz<br /><br />...which is <strong>closer</strong> to 240Hz.<br /><br />So shouldn't we be using 89489 ??<br /><br />pz!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3962">jwdonal</a> — Tue Dec 28, 2010 2:29 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
